## Copy Button Pattern (`ui/src/pages/dashboard-tools.ts`)

A `_clipboardWrite(text, successMsg)` helper handles all clipboard operations with a `navigator.clipboard` → `execCommand('copy')` fallback:

```javascript
/**
 * @param {string} text
 * @param {string} [successMsg]
 */
async function _clipboardWrite(text, successMsg = 'Copied!') {
    if (navigator.clipboard && window.isSecureContext) {
        await navigator.clipboard.writeText(text);
        notify(successMsg, 'success');
    } else {
        // execCommand fallback for non-HTTPS / older browsers
        const ta = document.createElement('textarea');
        ta.value = text;
        ta.style.cssText = 'position:fixed;top:-9999px;left:-9999px';
        document.body.appendChild(ta);
        ta.select();
        document.execCommand('copy');
        document.body.removeChild(ta);
        notify(successMsg, 'success');
    }
}
```

**Every tool's copy button must:**
1. Use `data-action="copyXxx"` (no inline `onclick`)
2. Call `_clipboardWrite` — never `navigator.clipboard` directly
3. For email tools: combine `subject` + `\n\n` + `body` in the copied text

