## Character Counter Pattern (Job Comparison)

For long-text inputs with a server-side char limit, add a live counter:

```html
<textarea id="job1Description" maxlength="5000" ...></textarea>
<div class="char-counter" id="job1CharCount">0 / 5000</div>
```

```javascript
// In DOMContentLoaded
['job1Description','job2Description','job3Description'].forEach(id => {
    const el = document.getElementById(id);
    const counter = document.getElementById(id.replace('Description','CharCount'));
    if (!el || !counter) return;
    el.addEventListener('input', () => {
        const len = /** @type {HTMLTextAreaElement} */ (el).value.length;
        counter.textContent = `${len} / 5000`;
        counter.classList.toggle('char-near-limit', len >= 4000 && len < 4900);
        counter.classList.toggle('char-at-limit', len >= 4900);
    });
});
```

CSS:
```css
.char-counter        { font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--text-muted); text-align: right; }
.char-near-limit     { color: var(--warning-color); }
.char-at-limit       { color: var(--danger-color); font-weight: 600; }
```

