## UI Output Structure (tools.html CSS classes)

All tool output sections follow the same sectioned card pattern as the application detail page.

### Email-style outputs (Thank You, Follow-up, Reference)
```
.followup-output-card      outer card container
.followup-subject          subject line box (muted bg, monospace-ish)
.followup-body             email body (pre-wrap)
.salary-content-section    reusable section block (border-top padding)
.salary-section-title      section heading with icon
```

### Rejection Analysis
```
.rejection-summary         summary paragraph box
.rejection-item            icon + text row for reasons/suggestions/signals
.rejection-item-icon       colored icon circle
.rejection-positive-card   green-tinted positive signals card
.encouragement-header      motivational header above positive signals
```

### Job Comparison
```
.comp-recommendation-card  top recommendation summary card
.comparison-grid           CSS grid for job cards (auto-fill, min 280px)
.comp-job-card             individual job card (dark bg, border-radius)
.comp-job-card--recommended  highlighted border for recommended job
.comp-job-body             card content area (no separate header band)
.comp-job-title-text       job title (prominent, inline with score badge)
.comp-job-score-badge      score pill (accent color)
.comp-pros-header          "Pros" subheader with + icon
.comp-cons-header          "Cons" subheader with − icon
.comp-job-list             ul for pros/cons items
.comp-ideal-for            "Ideal for: ..." footer line
.decision-factor-row       row in the decision factors table
.decision-factor-name      factor name (left col)
.decision-factor-winner    winning job identifier (center)
.decision-factor-importance importance badge (High/Med/Low)
.decision-factor-explanation  explanation text (muted, small)
```

**Job cards have NO separate header band.** Title, company in parentheses, and score badge are all rendered inline inside `.comp-job-body`:
```html
<div class="comp-job-body">
  <div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:flex-start;gap:0.5rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
    <div class="comp-job-title-text">Founding Engineer <span>(Weekday YC W21)</span></div>
    <span class="comp-job-score-badge">84/100</span>
  </div>
  ...
</div>
```
Company is always shown in parentheses after the title — even when titles are unique — for clarity.

